The '''Withered Dale''' was the name of the valley where [[Tevildo]] encountered [[Huan]] according to the early version of the [[legendarium]] in ''[[The Book of Lost Tales]]''.<ref name=LT2IN>{{LT2|In}}, p. 56</ref>

== History ==
The Withered Dale was a wide valley that was shaped "''like a bowl among the rocks''". Nothing grew there except for withered grass and some low bushes with only a few leaves.<ref name=LT2I>{{LT2|I}}</ref>{{rp|48}} The valley lay slightly less than a mile westwards of the [[halls of Tevildo]].<ref name=LT2I/>{{rp|15-6}} [[Tinúviel]] told Tevildo of Huan lying injured in the woods nearby. Tevildo's fell for Tinúviel's ruse and he followed her with two of his thanes, one of which was [[Oikeroi]].<ref name=LT2I/>{{rp|41-5}} It was here where [[Tevildo]] had encountered [[Huan]], who was pretending to be wounded, lying in a bank of fern. Huan killed Oikeroi, the other thane fled, and Tevildo himself fled up a tall and smooth tree near the valley.<ref name=LT2I/>{{rp|27-8}}

